<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="to">Churchill</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d152fn1">The source text bears the following typed notation:
                                “Above message sent by the President from Tunis to the Prime
                                Minister at Cairo thru local channels.”</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tunis</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-21">21 November 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Personal and Secret for the Prime Minister from the President.</p>
                        <p>Thank you very much for your messages Numbers 502,<note n="2" xml:id="d152fn2"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_81">p. 81</ref>.</note> 503,<note n="3" xml:id="d152fn3"><hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_188">p.
                                188</ref>.</note> 504<note n="4" xml:id="d152fn4"><hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_189">p. 189</ref>.</note> and
                                505<note n="5" xml:id="d152fn5"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_85">p. 85</ref>.</note> which were delivered to me
                            upon my arrival early yesterday. I expect to reach <gloss target="#t_Sextant1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Sextant</hi></gloss> early
                            morning November twenty-second, and it will be grand to see you again. I
                            hope your cold is better.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RFD1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>